Let's say with `n` being `3` you have this loop:


for(i = 0; i < n; i++)
    print i;


the result will be: 012


Now we put a loop inside of the loop


for(i = 0; i < n; i++){
    for(j = 0; j < n; j++){
        print i;

    }

}



the result will be: 000111222


The amount of operations has been squared, hence n^2. If you'd put another loop in this one, it would be n^3.

